17@3@The servant, however, thought he intended by that to say: "That is the first thief," and as he actually was so, he was terrified, and said to his comrade outside: "The doctor knows all: we shall fare ill, he said I was the first."
18@3@The second did not want to go in at all, but was forced.
20@3@This servant was equally alarmed, and he got out as fast as he could.
26@3@On this the servants looked terribly uneasy, and made a sign to the doctor that they wished him to step outside for a moment.
33@3@Then the fellow in the stove thought that the doctor meant him, and full of terror, sprang out, crying: "That man knows everything!"
